      "applicationProcess": [
        {
          "mode": "Offline",
          "process": [
            {
              "type": "align_justify",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "block_quote",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "In Rural Areas:",
                      "bold": true,
                      "underline": true
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Step 1:",
                      "bold": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " The applicant, who fulfills the eligibility criteria, may visit the office of the Gram Panchayat and collect the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "link": "https://sw.cg.gov.in/sites/default/files/pensionscheme.pdf",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "application form"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ", which is available free of cost."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Step 2:",
                      "bold": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " Fill out the application form and submit it to the Gram Panchayat. You will receive an acknowledgment receipt from the Gram Panchayat."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Step 3:",
                      "bold": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " The Gram Panchayat will review and recommend the application and then forward it to the District Panchayat within 07 days."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "block_quote",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "In Urban Areas:",
                      "bold": true,
                      "underline": true
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Step 1:",
                      "bold": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " Eligible applicants should visit the office of the concerned Municipal Corporation, Municipality, Nagar Panchayat, or Panchayat Raj institution to collect the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "link": "https://sw.cg.gov.in/sites/default/files/pensionscheme.pdf",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "application form"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ", which is available free of cost."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Step 2:",
                      "bold": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " Fill out the application form and submit it to the respective office (Municipality/Municipal Corporation/Nagar Panchayat). You will receive an acknowledgment receipt from the office."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Note 1:",
                      "bold": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " The concerned urban body/District Panchayat has the authority to approve or reject the applications."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Note 2:",
                      "bold": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " If a printed application form is not available, you may submit your application on plain paper."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "process_md": "&gt; **In Rural Areas:**\n\n**Step 1:** The applicant, who fulfills the eligibility criteria, may visit the office of the Gram Panchayat and collect the [application form](https://sw.cg.gov.in/sites/default/files/pensionscheme.pdf), which is available free of cost.\n**Step 2:** Fill out the application form and submit it to the Gram Panchayat. You will receive an acknowledgment receipt from the Gram Panchayat.\n**Step 3:** The Gram Panchayat will review and recommend the application and then forward it to the District Panchayat within 07 days.\n&gt; **In Urban Areas:**\n\n**Step 1:** Eligible applicants should visit the office of the concerned Municipal Corporation, Municipality, Nagar Panchayat, or Panchayat Raj institution to collect the [application form](https://sw.cg.gov.in/sites/default/files/pensionscheme.pdf), which is available free of cost.\n**Step 2:** Fill out the application form and submit it to the respective office (Municipality/Municipal Corporation/Nagar Panchayat). You will receive an acknowledgment receipt from the office.\n**Note 1:** The concerned urban body/District Panchayat has the authority to approve or reject the applications.\n**Note 2:** If a printed application form is not available, you may submit your application on plain paper.\n"
        },
